## Pre-class task: review data structure
- Look at `SubjectID` and `DayName`: how were controls matched?  
- How many controls per case?  
- How many cases are in the dataset?  
- How many strata (matched case-control sets)?  
- What is the average PM2.5 among cases? Among controls?  

*Hints:* `unique()` counts unique values; `length()` counts elements.

> **Answer key (how to verify in code)**
>
> - **How were controls matched?** Inspect `DayName` (e.g., same day-of-week within a time stratum such as month) and confirm controls share the same `SubjectID` as the case.
> - **Controls per case:** Typically fixed (often 3–4) in a time-stratified case-crossover; compute from the data with the code below.
>
> ```{r}
> # how many rows per SubjectID? (case + controls)
> dta %>%
>   count(SubjectID) %>%
>   summarise(min_n = min(n), max_n = max(n), median_n = median(n))
>
> # controls per case (assuming 1 case per SubjectID)
> dta %>%
>   group_by(SubjectID) %>%
>   summarise(n_case = sum(Case == 1), n_ctrl = sum(Case == 0), .groups = "drop") %>%
>   summarise(
>     median_ctrl = median(n_ctrl),
>     min_ctrl = min(n_ctrl),
>     max_ctrl = max(n_ctrl)
>   )
>
> # how many cases / strata?
> n_cases  <- sum(dta$Case == 1)
> n_strata <- n_distinct(dta$SubjectID)
> c(n_cases = n_cases, n_strata = n_strata)
>
> # mean PM among cases vs controls
> dta %>%
>   group_by(Case) %>%
>   summarise(mean_pm = mean(dailyPM, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop")
> ```

:::

