## 6. Non-linearity in case-crossover (covered in more detail in Week 4)

### 6a. Fit a natural spline for PM2.5 

```{r}
mod.clogit.ns3 <- clogit(
  Case ~ ns(dailyPM, df = 3) + ns(dailyTemp, df = 3) + ns(dailyRH, df = 4) +
    strata(SubjectID),
  method = "efron",
  data = dta
)

summary(mod.clogit.ns3)
```

### 6b. Plot non-linear exposure–response (PM spline)

```{r}
ptemp <- predict(mod.clogit.ns3, type = "terms", se.fit = TRUE)
ptemp <- as.data.frame(ptemp)

dta.pred <- bind_cols(dta, ptemp)

pm_term_col <- grep("dailyPM|PM", names(ptemp), value = TRUE)[1]
pm_se_col   <- grep("se", names(ptemp), value = TRUE)[1]

dta.pred <- dta.pred %>%
  mutate(
    term_pm = .data[[pm_term_col]],
    se_pm   = .data[[pm_se_col]],
    fit.or  = exp(term_pm),
    lci.or  = exp(term_pm - 1.96 * se_pm),
    uci.or  = exp(term_pm + 1.96 * se_pm)
  )

dta.pred %>%
  sample_frac(0.1) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = dailyPM)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = fit.or), linewidth = 1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = lci.or), linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_line(aes(y = uci.or), linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_rug(alpha = 0.3) +
  xlab(expression("Daily PM"[2.5])) +
  ylab("Odds of CVD admission")
```

### 6c. Compare model fit (AIC)

```{r}
AIC(mod.clogit.lin)
AIC(mod.clogit.ns3)
```

::: {.callout-question}
## Class question 4
Based on the plot, describe the exposure–response relationship qualitatively.  

> **Answer key** 
>
> **Qualitative shape:** PM2.5 is associated with **increasing** CVD hospitalizations for PM2.5 **up to ~10 µg/m³**, then a plateau (as shown in the spline plot).
:::

